'''Uranium''' was a [[Radiation/Legends|radioactive]] heavy metal<ref name="SWS" /> used to power facilities.<ref name="DS" /> The decay of uranium, when occurring within a planet, heated the rock of the planet's crust.<ref name="DF:SE" />

The [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ruusan/Legends|Ruusan]] had significant deposits of uranium,<ref name="DF:JK" /> as did [[Sullust/Legends|Sullust's]] [[Moon/Legends|moon]], [[Sulon/Legends|Sulon]].<ref name="DF:SE" /> [[Moorjhone]] was home to uranium mines run by [[Rim Commercial Mining]] which supplied uranium to power plants from [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] to the [[Tingel Arm/Legends|Tingel Arm]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="DS" /> [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] once won a half-million [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credit]] uranium mine in a [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] game. However, the accounts were so crooked that he was lucky to escape prosecution when the shareholders investigated the business.<ref name="RD">''[[Rebel Dawn]]''</ref> At some point, he owned a two-million-credit uranium mine that he lost playing sabacc.<ref name="SWS" />

[[Hoersch-Kessel ion drive|Hoersch-Kessel ion engines]], the most popular [[Ion engine/Legends|ion drive]] in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], could be converted to draw power from uranium and other heavy metals by breaking down the elements.<ref name="SWS2E">[[The Star Wars Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''The Star Wars Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref> [[Starfighter/Legends|Starfighter]] [[Fuel cell/Legends|fuel cells]] were comprised of refined radioactive metal mixes,<ref name="RASB2">[[The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref> including [[plutonium]] and uranium.<ref name="RASB">''[[The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook]]''</ref> The biology of an [[Exogorth/Legends|Exogorth]] contained a uranium-based metabolism.<ref name="VD">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
In ''[[The Star Wars Sourcebook]]'', uranium is stated to be one of the best sources to power a [[Hoersch-Kessel ion drive]].<ref name="SWS" /> When the information was reprinted in the [[The Star Wars Sourcebook (Second Edition)|second edition]] of the sourcebook, this information was updated to state that the Hoersch-Kessel ion drive could be converted to draw power from uranium and other heavy metals but was primarily powered by [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]] and [[Power generator/Legends|power generators]].<ref name="SWS2E" />

